=== Noun ===

'''Accomplice''' [Ac- (perh. for the article a or for L. ad) + E. [[complice]]. See [[Complice]].]

#A [[cooperator]]. [R.]

#:<code>Success unto our valiant general, And happiness to his ''accomplices''! ''[[Shakespeare (source)|Shakespeare]].''</code>

#''(Law)'' An associate in the commission of a crime; a [[participator]] in an offense, whether a principal or an [[accessory]].

#:<code>And thou, the cursed ''accomplice'' of his treason.</code> ''[[Johnson (source)|Johnson]].'' It is followed by ''with'' or ''of'' before a person and by ''in'' (or sometimes ''of'') before the crime; as, A was an ''accomplice'' with B in the [[murder]] of C. Dryden uses it with ''to'' before a thing.

<code>Suspected for ''accomplice'' to the fire.</code> ''[[Dryden (source)|Dryden]].''

